Image Source : PTI big news! BCCI is going to take a big decision soon BCCI to Increase Domestic Players salary: IPL is the richest cricket league in the world. Players playing in this league get huge amount of money. Meanwhile, a big news is coming out. The Board of Control for Cricket in India is soon going to take a big decision for the players playing domestic cricket. BCCI is considering a special plan for the players who are not playing in the IPL. Salaries of domestic players may increase soon. <!-- /8323530/Khabar_Desktop_VDO_1X1 --> BCCI is going to take a big decision soon According to a report by Cricbuzz, the Board of Control for Cricket in India may soon increase the salary of players playing domestic cricket. Ajit Agarkar’s selection committee has been entrusted with the task of giving suggestions regarding its implementation. According to reports, BCCI believes that the fees of domestic cricketers should be at least double. The board can give Rs 75 lakh to Rs 1 crore as annual salary to players who play 10 Ranji Trophy matches. What is the salary of domestic players now? At present, salary is given on the basis of experience in domestic cricket. BCCI pays Rs 60,000 per day to players who play more than 40 Ranji games, Rs 50,000 to those who play 21 to 40 games and Rs 40,000 to those who play 20 matches. At this pay scale, a senior cricketer earns up to Rs 25 lakh if his team reaches the finals, while other players in the team earn between Rs 17 lakh and Rs 22 lakh. BCCI wants to promote red ball cricket BCCI is working on promoting red ball cricket. BCCI has recently started an incentive scheme in Test cricket to promote red ball cricket. Under this, the match fees of players who play more than 75% of the tests in a year will increase by 300%. At the same time, BCCI had recently asked the players included in the central contract to play domestic cricket. In such a situation, BCCI is bringing new schemes to promote domestic cricket. read this also T20 